commit.message:
makefile: fix parallel build failures due to missing objdirs

The error is best reproducible with GNU make 4.4's `make --shuffle`
build:

    $ make --shuffle
    ...
    Fatal error: can't create bin-blahtex/Messages.o: No such file or directory

The build fails because $(BINDIR) is not ready yet.
Add $(BINDIR) to dependencies of all object files.
use WIN32 API instead of iconv at MinGW
Support sizeof(wchar_t) == 2 environment, like as MinGW

Merge pull request #3 from mattrajca/master

Fixed regressions, added more unit tests, report more errors

added unit tests

caught a regression in \mathbb rendering
